The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, has vowed to run a true government of the people by the people and for the people if elected in next Saturday’s election. Tinubu was speaking at the party’s presidential campaign rally in Maiduguri, Borno State, Saturday, February 18, when he reiterated that he would run a government of hard work, honesty and accountability in managing the country’s affairs. He expressed joy for the turnout of the people of the state to the campaign rally. The party’s National Chairman, Abdullahi Adamu, also expressed delight at the turnout of the people of the state to the rally. Expressing confidence in the ability of the party to win the election, Adamu said, “Nothing, apart from the will of God, will deprive us of victory in the election.” Governor Babagana Zulum expressed confidence that Tinubu would uphold the trust of the people of the state. Governors Abdullahi Ganduje, Mai Mala Buni, Muhammadu Badaru, Inuwa Yahaya and Abdullahi Sule of Kano, Yobe, Jigawa, Gombe and Nasarawa states attended the rally.